+## WALLET-210 211 Service Partner Pilot Rehearsal
+
+Run this rehearsal in staging before a service-partner pilot. Use synthetic
+records and a non-production partner DID. Archive status metadata and reviewed
+screenshots only; do not archive plaintext, precise coordinates, proof
+witnesses, private keys, bearer tokens, or storage credentials.
+
+Required setup:
+
+- The target API uses durable staging repository and encrypted blob storage.
+- The UI is configured for the same API origin through the wallet query
+  parameters or environment-specific routing.
+- `WALLET_SERVICES_JSONL` points at the service directory used for the pilot.
+- The proof mode matches the current launch gate: development-mode simulated
+  proofs for repository automation, or production-mode external verifier only
+  after WALLET-180 cutover evidence is archived.
+- The analytics template used in the demo is approved under the WALLET-200
+  governance workflow, or the rehearsal template is clearly marked staging-only
+  with `min_cohort_size=1` for synthetic data.
+
+Rehearsal sequence:
+
+1. Create a synthetic wallet and open the UI as the owner. From Uploads, add an
+   intake document and confirm the visible record status is saved.
+2. Add a synthetic precise location through
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations`; keep only the returned location
+   `record_id` in the demo notes.
+3. Create a partner `record/analyze` grant with an explicit pilot purpose and
+   redacted output caveats. Open Recipient Access as the partner, run redacted
+   analysis, and confirm direct identifiers are absent.
+4. Create a coarse-location grant and invocation, call
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/services/match`, and confirm the result contains
+   service reasons but not precise latitude or longitude.
+5. Open Proof Center as the owner, create a `location_region` proof for the
+   location record, and confirm the public inputs contain region and policy/hash
+   values only.
+6. Create analytics consent from the approved template, submit one allowed
+   derived-field contribution, and release only the approved aggregate count.
+7. Revoke the partner grant, refresh Recipient Access, and verify the receipt is
+   revoked and any old invocation is rejected.
+8. Open Audit and verify the timeline includes record add, grant create,
+   invocation issue/verify, redacted analysis, coarse-location read, proof
+   create, analytics consent/contribution/query, and grant revoke events.
+
+Pass criteria:
+
+- Every archived UI or API artifact contains descriptors, IDs, hashes, public
+  proof inputs, consent/template IDs, aggregate counts, or status metadata only.
+- Redacted analysis and export evidence do not contain names, emails, phone
+  numbers, SSNs, street addresses, precise coordinates, or full document text.
+- The audit timeline can reconstruct the workflow without relying on app-local
+  browser state.
+- Revoked partner access fails through the same public API surface that
+  previously allowed the action.
+
+Local validation:
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/test_wallet_interface_api.py tests/test_wallet_third_party_blackbox.py -q
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui run build
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
